Rent a house near the beach, or a cabinbut: Do not take your walking shoes.Don’t take any clothes you’d wearanyplace anyone would see you.Don’t take your rechargeables.Take Scrabble if you have to,but not a dictionary and nopencils for keeping score.Don’t take a cookbookor anything to cook.A fishing pole, okbut not the line,hook, sinker,leave it all.Find outwhat’sleft. • How to Fly (In Ten Thousand Easy Lessons) by Barbara Kingsolver is published by Faber (£14.99). To order a copy go to guardianbookshop.com. Delivery charges may apply.